A man, whose identity is yet to be ascertained, has been stabbed to death in his house at Abaku, Osogbo, the Osun State capital. The corpse of the man was found in the house by his neighbours, who reported the incident to the police. A source told Daily Trust that the deceased had attended the Osun Osogbo festival last week and might have been involved in a fight that broke out among touts, in which a man known as Olota Faasi was killed. Meanwhile, the state governor, Mr Gboyega Oyetola, has appealed to traditional worshipers in the state to be peaceful and law-abiding during and after the Isese festival. Oyetola has declared today as a public holiday to mark this year traditional worshippers’ day, tagged ‘Isese Day’ in the state.  Osun declares Monday  public holiday for Traditional Worshipers Day Thrills and frills of the Osun Osogbo festival Countdown to Osun 2018: 14 contenders to watch Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin